programme.desc: Until recently most scientists thought they knew what killed off the dinosaurs. It was a 10 km-wide meteorite which smashed into Yucatan in Mexico.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Exploring Mongolia's Gobi Desert to determine whether dinosaurs exist in the present as birds. It is one of the harshest places on Earth with the biggest dinosaur graveyard.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Horizon follows scientists across the world on a quest to solve the riddle of the Hobbit.
programme.sub-title: The Mystery of the Human Hobbit

programme.title: Deadly Dinosaurs
programme.desc: Steve is going large as he focuses on the biggest animals to have ever walked the earth. In his dino-den, he starts by meeting the Argentinosaurus, an animal so large that even its poo was deadly.

programme.title: Deadly Dinosaurs
programme.desc: The Jurassic was home to the most vicious and violent predators the world has ever seen. To survive, herbivores had to fight back. Steve Backshall goes on a mission to track down the deadliest of all dinosaur defenders.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Madagascar: Islands of Monsters
programme.desc: Madagascar is truly a weird and wonderful land. Isolated on an island of extreme and magical looking locations, life has adapted and diversified. With few predators, numbers have proliferated and natural selection has gone mad.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice
programme.desc: Mount Kenya soars over 5km into the air. It is the second highest mountain in Africa. At its summit, temperatures fluctuate from over 30 degrees celsius to below freezing.
programme.sub-title: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time
programme.desc: Namibia is an arid, rough land. However, it has been inhabited for thousands of years, by people as well as animals, and shows no sign of losing popularity with either.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Zambezi: Wild Water
programme.desc: The Zambezi is one of Africa's most influential rivers. It supports some of the continent's most spectacular wildlife. However, the Zambezi's long and winding journey destroys, as well as creates.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Vancouver Island: Rivers of Life
programme.desc: Vancouver island is the largest island off the west coast of North America. Glaciers fuel the flow of some of Canada's tallest waterfalls, and an endless network of rivers and creeks provides the ideal habitat for the pacific salmon.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise
programme.desc: The Caribbean is a tropical paradise. From just a few meters wide, to hundreds of kilometers across, each of the over 7,000 islands are different, and each has its own unique wildlife.
programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island
programme.desc: Lying like a teardrop in the Indian Ocean, Sri Lanka is an island that defies convention. Poised just six degrees above the equator, it's less than 75,000 km sq in size. But it has enough wildlife to rival a continent.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Falkland Islands: Penguin Paradise
programme.desc: The Falkland's bleak, battered, and windswept archipelago lies 460 km from the South American mainland. Rugged mountains and expansive pristine coastline are a unique home for wildlife  especially for one of the world's most iconic flightless birds.

programme.title: Anything But Christmas
programme.desc: Just days before Christmas, a Kentucky State Representative proposes a bill to change the holiday's name from Christmas to something more inclusive. But if they change the name, what will they call it? No one seems to know, just Anything BUT Christmas.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: El Niño
programme.desc: It is estimated that between 1997 and 1998, “El Niño” took the lives of 24,000 people and created a startling $34 billion (US) in economic damages worldwide. In this episode we explain what “El Niño” is.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Tsunamis
programme.desc: In Japanese, Tsunami translates to “harbour wave.” They are unleashed when a major disturbance occurs underwater, creating a series of enormous, deadly swells.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Hurricanes
programme.desc: With a combination of torrential rain, powerful winds, and devastating storm surges, Hurricanes are among Mother Nature’s most calamitous natural disasters.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Cyclones
programme.desc: An intense area of low pressure that forms over warm tropical waters, tropical cyclones are responsible for some of the most catastrophic extreme weather events. Their deadly winds and torrential rain wreak destruction on an unprecedented scale.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Mosquitoes
programme.desc: In 2014, Microsoft Founder Bill Gates described the mosquito as the “deadliest animal in the world.” It is estimated by the World Health Organisation that they kill roughly 750,000 people per year.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Floods
programme.desc: Even when below your knees, you can still be swept off your feet by the torrent of water. And the danger doesn’t stop there: electric shocks, contaminated water and washed away vehicles are perilous.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Famine
programme.desc: Every continent on Earth has experienced this terrifying phenomenon at some point in its history. It’s ravaged the world for centuries, as crop infestation, drought, flooding and disease have killed thousands.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Wild Weather Season
programme.desc: 2005 seemed to be the year that Earth went wild. Follow George as he brings us back to the site of his hairiest adventures from that year.

programme.title: Angry Planet: West Coast Winter Weather
programme.desc: On Canada's rugged West Coast, George ice-climbs a frozen waterfall, uses ski-skins to climb Mt.Garibaldi to an alpine lake, visits a storm-watching lodge on British Columbia's Long Beach, home of winter surfing and massive Pacific storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Waterspouts
programme.desc: In the Florida Keys, George uses a motorboat, a van and small plane to get up close to waterspouts - the nautical cousins of tornadoes. He also meets some of the 25 million alligators that live in the Sunshine State.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Island Caving
programme.desc: Accompanied by a group of hardcore cavers from Alberta and British Columbia, George descends into spectacular caves that lead deep into the earth on Vancouver Island. The team carries inflatable kayaks to explore a dark underground river.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Desert Monsoon
programme.desc: Enlisting the help of fellow storm chaser R.J. Evans, George heads to Arizona to photograph spectacular lightning storms triggered by the desert monsoon season. R.J. however is known as "America's noisiest athiest" for his free-thought radio show.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Polynesian Volcanoes
programme.desc: In New Zealand, George learns that an undersea volcano 1000 miles North in Tonga is creating a new island. After nautical mishaps, clad in nothing but underwear and a life jacket, George becomes one of the first explorers on this new land.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Java: Land of Fire
programme.desc: In the Pacific Ring of Fire island of Java, George explores new ash eruptions from Anak Krakatau, whose 1883 eruption shook the world. He travels to Merapi and descends into Kawah Ijen to explore the world's largest lake of sulfuric acid.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Highway to Hail
programme.desc: George and his team head into "bears' cage", looking to get beat up by the biggest, baddest hailstones in Texas and Oklahoma. Their storm chasing vehicles don't look too pretty after coming through these massive storms.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Costa Rica
programme.desc: George explores the volcanoes of Costa Rica with an international team of scientists, rafts down white water rivers in full flood, rappels down raging waterfalls, and handles some of deadliest snakes this tropical country has to offer.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Winds Of Autumn
programme.desc: This year he starts off by getting prepared in a wind tunnel, then he and his chase partner Mark Robinson head to Newfoundland for more wild weather action. Then, it's off to another encounter where the wild wind fans a raging inferno.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Iceland: Fire and Ice
programme.desc: George meets President of Iceland Ólafur Grímsson who spearheaded use of geothermal power; visits Blue Lagoon and geysers; explores volcanically active Haimaey Island and climbs an iceberg calving off the glaciers at Vatnajokull Lagoon.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Hurricane Triple Threat
programme.desc: George chases deadly hurricanes in the USA: Gustav in Louisiana and Hanna in North Carolina. He then flies with USAF Hurricane Hunters into Ike over Cuba, meeting it again as it makes a wild destructive landfall in Galveston, Texas.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Timbuktu: Birthplace of Hurricanes
programme.desc: Dust storms can spin off from Africa into the Atlantic and morph into tropical hurricanes that threaten the Caribbean and USA. While searching for Timbuktu's dust storms, George finds adventure in the landscape and culture of West Africa.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Antarctica
programme.desc: From "Fin Del Mundo," George sails on a Russian icebreaker to Antarctica. After braving stormy Drake passage, he explores volcanic Deception Island, camps in Antarctic snow and paddles a kayak through icebergs calved off melting glaciers.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Eco-Disasters
programme.desc: Uzbekistan's Aral Sea, once one of the largest freshwater lakes in the world, shrunk to 1/6 its previous size; a Crimea mountain carved into a submarine base; Chernobyl nuclear site reduced to a radioactive wasteland.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Under Pressure

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanic Islands
programme.desc: They've been worshiped and feared over the millennia. But in the wake of drama and destruction, the elements give rise to cultures and nations so beautiful that we've come to know them as the world's greatest volcanic islands.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Port Cities
programme.desc: Some of the most stunning cities are port cities - Sydney, Rio, Cape Town - and are also some of the most culturally diverse and vibrant. The great maritime cities of the world bridge countries and continents and unite the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: Destroy Paris: Hitler's Secret Plan
programme.desc: By 1944, as the Reich was crumbling, Hitler gave detailed orders for the destruction of Paris. He wanted the monuments and all the bridges mined and the city reduced to a 'pile of rubble'.

programme.title: Battle of Britain: The Race For Radar
programme.desc: On the brink of war the Germans mount a daring Zeppelin spy mission. Had the Luftwaffe spies discovered Britain’s greatest secret?'

programme.title: Battle for the Bulge
programme.desc: The Battle for the Bulge was the last major German offensive move on the Western Front during the Second World War.

programme.title: Rommel: The Soldier, The Son, and Hitler
programme.desc: Never a member of the Nazi party, Rommel detested blending politics and war. He would quickly discover that both were always in play under Hitler.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Building The Brand
programme.desc: Hitler’s fascination with propaganda was born in the trenches of the First World War. There he saw it emerge as a potent tool of psychological warfare - one that he would harness to build the Nazi movement. Witness Hitler's early propaganda tactics.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Power and Persuasion
programme.desc: This episode explores Hitler's approach to propaganda in power; where persuasion was achieved through propaganda and terror, all in service of one goal: the creation of a state under one shared ideology. A new German power fueled by propaganda.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Why We Fight
programme.desc: This episode explores the way Hitler used propaganda to justify his warmongering, reframing it as defense of Germany’s people and borders. It investigates the role propaganda played for both Hitler and the Allies to mobilize their countries for war.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The fourth episode sees the Germans well and truly on the retreat and the Allies are able to successfully implement operation Husky: the landing on Sicily.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The third episode opens with Rommel’s second offensive in North Africa.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: The second episode starts on the morning of the 22nd of June 1941 when the Germans launched operation Barbarossa, the code name for the invasion of the Soviet Union.

programme.title: NEW: Great Tank Battles of World War II
programme.desc: This first part of the series introduces the first tanks being deployed on the battlefields in northern France during WWI and describes the devastating effect these steel monsters had on an infantry confronted with them for the very first time.

programme.title: Gestapo: Hitler's Secret Police
programme.desc: Hermann Goering’s Secret State Police were tasked to arrest and torture confessions and information from supposed enemies of the Reich.

programme.title: Embedded 45' - Shooting War in Germany: Embedded 45 - Shooting War in Germany 2
programme.desc: This second episode covers the last week of March to late April. The cameramen covered many stories of victory and defeat, death and liberation. Faces of despair and joy, scenes of war and peace.

programme.title: Embedded 45' - Shooting War in Germany: Embedded 45 - Shooting War in Germany 1
programme.desc: This first episode covers the last week of February to late March. When American troops started their final invasion of Nazi Germany in February 1945, U.S. Army cameramen were at their side.

programme.title: Destroy Paris: Hitler's Secret Plan
programme.desc: By 1944, as the Reich was crumbling, Hitler gave detailed orders for the destruction of Paris. He wanted the monuments and all the bridges mined and the city reduced to a 'pile of rubble'.

programme.title: Battle of Britain: The Race For Radar
programme.desc: On the brink of war the Germans mount a daring Zeppelin spy mission. Had the Luftwaffe spies discovered Britain’s greatest secret?'

programme.title: Christmas Encore
programme.desc: Charlotte Lacy ist eine verzweifelte Schauspielerin, die die Hauptrolle in einer Produktion von "A Christmas Carol" ergattert. Sie und der Regisseur haben jedoch viele unterschiedliche kreative Vorstellungen.

programme.title: Weihnachten in den Highlands
programme.desc: Dieses Weihnachten wird Blair Henderson, eine Parfümexpertin aus New York, von ihrer Chefin ins ferne Schottland geschickt, um einen seltenen Duft zu finden.

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek
programme.desc: Eine junge Chefin kehrt in ihre Heimatstadt zurück, um die Bedeutung von Weihnachten wiederzuentdecken.

programme.title: Weihnachten in der Holly Lane
programme.desc: Die Kindheitsfreundinnen Sarah, Riley und Cat kehren als Erwachsene in ihre Heimatstadt zurück und erinnern sich an die glücklichen Weihnachtsfeste, die sie gemeinsam verbrachten. Sie wollen den Weihnachtszauber von früher wieder zum Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Holly Maddux fehlt zu ihrem Glück nur noch der perfekte Mann. Nach einem Sturz vor dem Geschäft schwebt Holly im siebten Himmel, denn ihr Traummann steht plötzlich vor ihr...

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Mistelzweige küsst man nicht
programme.desc: Zu Weihnachten kehrt Darcy nach Hause zurück und läuft dort ihrem Highschool-Erzfeind Luke über den Weg. Als beide bei der Vorbereitung einer weihnachtlichen Wohltätigkeitsgala helfen, erkennen sie, dass ihre bisherige Abneigung womöglich voreilig war.

programme.title: Christmas in Boston
programme.desc: Gina und Seth sind seit ihrer Kindheit Brieffreunde, haben sich aber noch nie getroffen. Als sie sich endlich dazu entschließen, sich zu treffen, braucht es allerdings ein wenig Weihnachtszauber, um ihre Liebe füreinander aufzudecken.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: Der magische Weihnachtsschmuck
programme.desc: Seit sie an Weihnachten sitzen gelassen wurde, hat Marie (Jessica Lowndes) mit dem Fest der Liebe abgeschlossen. Daran kann auch der Festtagsschmuck nichts ändern, den ihre Mutter ihr täglich zukommen lässt.

programme.title: Weihnachten in Glenbrooke – Verliebt in die Millionärin
programme.desc: Jessica, Millionen-Erbin und bald CEO eines mächtigen Unternehmens, ist trotz ihres privilegierten Lebens unglücklich. Inkognito reist sie in den kleinen Geburtsort ihrer Mutter, um dort Weihnachten zu verbringen...

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Sabrina - Total verhext!: Salem auf Abwegen
programme.desc: Eine Entführung an Heiligabend lässt Salems Liebe zu seiner Familie wieder aufleben.

programme.title: Sabrina - Total verhext!: Das Weihnachtsfräulein
programme.desc: Ein besonderer Besucher aus dem anderen Reich hilft Sabrina, den wahren Geist der Weihnacht wiederzufinden.

programme.title: Sabrina - Total verhext!: Coole Weihnachten
programme.desc: Es sieht schon sehr nach Weihnachten aus, bis Sabrina versehentlich den Feiertag löscht.

programme.title: Sabrina - Total verhext!: Eiskalt erwischt
programme.desc: Eine lebensbedrohliche Situation zwingt Sabrina dazu, ihre Magie vor einem Hexenjäger zu offenbaren.

programme.title: Sabrina - Total verhext!: Zum Schmelzen schön
programme.desc: Als das Wetter draußen furchtbar wird, planen die Spellmans eine Reise nach Jamaika.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: O Natal Prometido
programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: O Verdadeiro Sentido do Amor
programme.desc: Na noite de Natal, o xerife Rick parece ter perdido seu espírito natalino. Quando prende um homem acusado de invadir as casas da vizinhança, o xerife não sabe o que fazer quando o invasor declara ser o Papai Noel em pessoa.

programme.title: O milagre de natal Jonathan Toomey
programme.desc: Quando um menino perde o presépio de madeira que o liga ao pai morto, sua mãe preocupada convence um entalhador solitário e mal-humorado a criar um substituto e permitir que seu filho o veja trabalhar nele.

programme.title: Tesouros de Família
programme.desc: Uma titereira falida volta para casa nas férias e se envolve em uma caça ao tesouro com sua melhor amiga obcecada por paintball, sua avó dançarina de tango e um namorado de infância.

programme.title: O Natal de James & Bob
programme.desc: Um músico de rua em dificuldades se vê alvo de uma investigação de bemestar animal que ameaça levar seu amado gato no Natal.

programme.title: Um Ano Depois Daquele Natal
programme.desc: Na sequência de “Eu Vou Casar Nesse Natal”, um ano se passou desde o noivado entre Marci e Blair. Mas, com o grande dia se aproximando, Marci tem trabalhado tanto que mal conseguiu planejar seu casamento.

programme.title: Uma Viagem Para Paris
programme.desc: Lucas, um rico empresário francês, vai a Montana para uma proposta de negócio muito atraente. Lá, ele conhece Robin, se apaixona e a leva para Paris em uma incrível aventura de Natal. Mas será que os negócios acabarão com esse romance?

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Golden Winter
programme.desc: Un chico se hace amigo de una camada de Golden Retrievers sin hogar. Juntos, ayudan a detener un robo a un banco justo a tiempo para Navidad.

programme.title: La navidad llega a casa
programme.desc: Un granjero viudo de Texas invita a su nuevo amor en Navidad para que conozca a su familia y descubre que la alegría navideña enmascara un deseo más profundo.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Golden Winter
programme.desc: Un chico se hace amigo de una camada de Golden Retrievers sin hogar. Juntos, ayudan a detener un robo a un banco justo a tiempo para Navidad.

programme.title: La navidad llega a casa
programme.desc: Un granjero viudo de Texas invita a su nuevo amor en Navidad para que conozca a su familia y descubre que la alegría navideña enmascara un deseo más profundo.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: La cabaña de Navidad
programme.desc: Mary se va de vacaciones a las montañas con su novio. De camino, encuentran a una niña que se había torcido el tobillo, y que casualmente es la hija de un antiguo amigo de su infancia.

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Golden Winter
programme.desc: Un chico se hace amigo de una camada de Golden Retrievers sin hogar. Juntos, ayudan a detener un robo a un banco justo a tiempo para Navidad.

programme.title: La navidad llega a casa
programme.desc: Un granjero viudo de Texas invita a su nuevo amor en Navidad para que conozca a su familia y descubre que la alegría navideña enmascara un deseo más profundo.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Un adivino le dice a una mujer con un problema de "fantasmas" en serie en aplicaciones de citas que debe resolver su pasado y hacer las paces con todos aquellos a quienes engañó antes de Navidad o estará destinada a nunca encontrar el amor verdadero.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: First Moments der besonderen Stars
programme.desc: Der herzliche Moderator Peter Grimberg geht den Geschichten, die das Leben schreibt, auf die Spur. In der Sendung ‚First Moments‘ reist er mit seinen prominenten Gästen in deren Vergangenheit und beleuchtet ihren ganz persönlichen Lebensweg. Freuen Sie sich auf Peter Kraus, Claudia Jung, Roberto Blanco und viele weitere prominente Gäste bei ‚First Moments‘.

programme.title: Howard Carpendale LIVE
programme.desc: Seit den späten 60er-Jahren ist Howard Carpendale regelmäßiger Gast in den Single- und Albumcharts in Deutschland. Bei GoldStar TV sehen Sie einen Konzertklassiker aus der Cottbusser Stadthalle von 2001. "Alles OK" hieß damals das Motto. Charmant und gut gelaunt wie eh und je stand Howard Carpendale dort auf der Bühne und präsentierte seine großen, zeitlosen Hits.

programme.title: Schlager & Co 4
programme.desc: Mit „Schlager & Co“ sind Sie immer am Puls der Zeit! Es erwarten Sie vielversprechende Nachwuchskünstler und die aktuellsten Hits deutscher Top-Interpreten. In „Schlager & Co“ zeigt GoldStar TV Ihnen alle brandneuen Schlagerhits vom Newcomer bis zum etablierten Star.

programme.title: GoldStar TV
programme.desc: GoldStar TV: Schlager und Evergreens, die man immer wieder gerne hört. Mit den Goldies geht es auf eine musikalische Zeitreise mit den besten Songs aus der "guten alten Zeit".

programme.title: Nigel Marvens wilde Philippinen
programme.desc: Die verstreuten Inseln Mindanao (die zweitgrößte der Philippinen), Bohol und Cebu beherbergen eine bizarre Vielfalt an Lebewesen und atemberaubende Landschaften. Nigel stellt uns Bohols weltberühmte Chocolate Hills vor, seltsame Hügel aus aufgelösten Korallen, die etwa 45 Millionen Jahre alt sind, und den legendären Mount Apo, wo der seltenste Adler der Welt sein Comeback feiert.

programme.title: Pinguine unter der Sonne Afrikas
programme.desc: In der Algoa Bay im Süden des afrikanischen Kontinents liegen die Brutinseln vieler Brillenpinguin-Kolonien. Sie sind die einzigen Pinguine, die unter der afrikanischen Sonne leben.

programme.title: Helden der Evolution
programme.desc: Diese Folge spürt rund um den Globus einige unserer nächsten Verwandten auf. Primaten jeder Größe haben ihren Auftritt, vom Zwergseidenäffchen im Amazonasbecken bis hin zum imposanten Mandrill in den Tropen Afrikas. Hier dient Körperpflege der Friedensstiftung, Gähnen ist ein Zeichen der Aggression, und manche Affen heben in ihren Backentaschen einen Snack für später auf.

programme.title: Helden der Evolution
programme.desc: Ob watschelnd, hüpfend oder schwimmend, die 18 Vertreter der allseits beliebten Pinguinfamilie sind skurril und doch vornehm anzusehen. Die torpedoförmigen, flugunfähigen Seevögel im schwarz-weißen Frack sind treu ergebene Partner, aufopfernde Eltern und schlaue Jäger. Es ist ein spektakulärer Anblick, wenn sie sich zu Hunderttausenden in Kolonien zusammenfinden

programme.title: Nigel Marvens wilde Philippinen
programme.desc: Die 15. größte Insel der Welt, aber die größte der Philippinen. Ein Land der Kontraste Von der Zersiedelung der Hauptstadt Manila bis hin zu riesigen versteckten Wäldern, den artenreichsten Riffen der Welt und einem Dutzend aktiver Vulkane, die die Skyline dominieren. Nigel trifft auf die außergewöhnlichen Kreaturen, die in diesen Landschaften leben.

programme.title: Nigel Marvens wilde Philippinen
programme.desc: Palawan, die westlichste Insel des Archipels, ist als letzte Grenze bekannt. Nigel wird seine alten Regenwälder, unberührten Küsten, Korallenriffe und unglaublichen unterirdischen Schätze erkunden.

programme.title: Herbie Hancock & The Headhunter
programme.desc: American keyboard player and bandleader Herbie Hancock (1940) achieved success as an incisive, harmonically provocative jazz pianist in the 1960s, then went on to gain wide popularity as a leader of electric jazz-rock groups. One of these, Hancock's band The Headhunters, ushered in a new era of jazz that appealed to a far wider audience, making jazz listeners out of rhythm and blues fans, and vice versa. In 1974, The Headhunters appeared on German television, playing Palm Grease, Sly, Butterfly, Spank-A-Lee, and Chameleon. Hancock (keys) is joined by Bennie Maupin (saxophones), Paul Jackson (electric bass), Mike Clark (drums) and Bill Summer (percussion).

programme.title: Ella Fitzgerald

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

programme.title: Trombone Shorty
programme.sub-title: Troy 'Trombone Shorty' Andrews: Jazz à Vienne
programme.desc: Jazz phenomenon Trombone Shorty dishes out a mix of funk, jazz, hip-hop and soul at this concert at the French festival Jazz à Vienne. Playing with the energy of a rock star, Troy Andrews, a.k.a. ‘Trombone Shorty', pays homage to jazz legends. With his hypnotic performance and boundless energy, Trombone Shorty puts up an unparalleled performance.

programme.title: Miles Davis
programme.desc: American trumpeter Miles Davis (1926-1991) was a pioneering jazz musician from the late 1940s to the late 1980s. His influence on 20th century music is hard to overstate, as he trailblazed bebop, cool jazz, hardbop, modal jazz, and electronic music. On October 11, 1964, Miles Davis performed at Teatro Dell'Arte in Milan. With tenor saxophonist Wayne Shorter, pianist Herbie Hancock, bassist Ron Carter and drummer Tony Williams, Davis performed Autumn Leaves, My Funny Valentine, All Blues, All of You, and Joshua.

programme.title: George Shearing & Neil Swanson
programme.sub-title: George Shearing Duo feat. Neil Swainson
programme.desc: British pianist George Shearing enjoyed an international reputation as an instrumentalist, arranger, and composer. Equally at home on the classical concert stage as in jazz clubs, he was recognized for his inventive, orchestrated jazz. In this live recording from the Munich Philharmonie, Shearing played in a duo format with Canadian double bassist Neil Swainson. The repertoire consisted of a selection of compositions by Shearing himself, among them ‘Lullaby Of Birdland', which is a standard in jazz repertoire.

programme.title: Cannonball Adderley, Nat Adderley, Yusuf Lateef & Joe Zawinul
programme.desc: Cannonball Adderley: Live in '63 boasts two beautifully filmed concerts from one of the most celebrated sextets in jazz history, captured at the top of their game. Cannonball Adderley (alto sax), Nat Adderley (cornet), and the masterful Yusef Lateef (tenor sax, flute, oboe), provide a massive three-horn frontline attack, while the stellar rhythm section featuring a pre-Weather Report Joe Zawinul (piano), Sam Jones (bass), and Louis Hayes (drums) fuel the songs with a deep infectious swing. Quincy Jones' "Jessica's Day" leaps from the gate with a huge big band sound that is extraordinary for only six musicians. This recording is a reminder that Cannonball Adderley was one of the most outstanding and highly respected alto saxophonists in the history of jazz. He was a bluesy jazzman who could play anything in superb fashion.

programme.title: Teen Idols
programme.desc: Rock music played on 45s became the soundtrack to the 1960s as people bought what they heard on the radio. 1960s teens were increasingly appreciating and emulating artists closer to their own age, to teen fashion, and to lyrics which addressed their own concerns. programme.title: David Bowie
programme.desc: David Bowie was the leading figure in popular music for over five decades. Acclaimed by critics and musicians for his innovative work. His career was marked by reinvention and visual presentation, his music and stagecraft significantly influencing popular music. During his lifetime, his record sales, estimated at 140 million albums worldwide, made him one of the bestselling music artists. He stopped concert touring after 2004 and his last live performance was at a charity event in 2006. In 2013, Bowie returned from a decade-long recording hiatus with the release of The Next Day. He remained musically active until his Death two days after the release of his final album, Blackstar.

programme.title: Michael Jackson
programme.desc: Michael Jackson American singer, songwriter, dancer and simply the King of Pop. His contributions to music, dance, and publicized personal life made him a global figure in popular culture for over four decades. Jackson made his professional debut in 1964 as a member of The Jackson 5, soon becoming a dominant figure in popular music. His music videos, “Beat It", “Billie Jean", and “Thriller" are credited with breaking racism in the USA and transforming the medium into an art form. Thriller is the best-selling album of all time. Jackson was the most awarded recording artist in the history of popular music. Aspects of Jackson's personal life generated controversy and while preparing for his comeback concert series, This Is It, Jackson died of acute Propofol and Benzodiazepine intoxication on June 25, 2009, after suffering from cardiac arrest. The Los Angeles County Department of Medical Examiner Coroner ruled his death a homicide, and his personal physician, Conrad Murray.

programme.title: Leonardo García Alarcón, Cappella Mediterranea & Mariana Flores
programme.sub-title: Vocal baroque works by Cavalli, Strozzi & Bembo
programme.desc: Argentinian conductor and harpsichordist Leonardo García Alarcón leads his ensemble Cappella Mediterranea in a program of Italian Baroque music. The ensemble performs some of the finest Baroque pieces composed by Francesco Cavalli, a prominent composer in 17th-century Venice, and two of his famous students, Barbara Strozzi and Antonia Bembo. Argentinian soprano Mariana Flores presents the vocal works. On the program are ‘Mira questi due lumi' from Cavalli's Le nozze di Teti e di Peleo, ‘Dimmi, Amor, che farò' from L'Oristeo, ‘Sinfonia della notte' from L'Egisto, and ‘E vuol dunque Ciprigna' from Ercole Amante ‘M'ingannasti in verità' from Bembo's Produzioni armoniche consacrate a Luigi XIV Strozzi's Sino alla morte, Che si può fare, Lagrime mie, L'amante segreto, and è Pazzo il moi core Biagio Marini's La Romanesca Tarquinio Merula's Aria Sopra La Cieccona and Dario Castello's Sonata Seconda. This performance was recorded at the magnificent Église Notre-Dame of Sablé-sur-Sarthe, France, on August 26, 2020.

programme.title: Les Arts Florissants & Paul Agnew
programme.desc: Italian composer Claudio Monteverdi (1567-1643) composed nine books of madrigals in half a century, which helped transform the genre from the polyphonic, a cappella madrigals of the late Renaissance to the ‘concertato' madrigals of the early Baroque, shifting the style's focus to the ability of music to express emotions contained in a text. In 2011, British tenor Paul Agnew and renowned Baroque ensemble Les Arts Florissants started recording eight books of Monteverdi's madrigals. In this program, Agnew leads Les Arts Florissants in the madrigals of Book I. Published on New Year's day of 1587, Book I consist of seventeen madrigals for five voices. This performance was recorded at the Cité de la musique in Paris, France, in 2011.

programme.title: Martha Argerich, Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shai & Arielle Beck
programme.sub-title: Martha Argerich – A Birthday Celebration - I
programme.desc: On the occasion of her 80th birthday, Argentinian pianist Martha Argerich explored chamber music repertoire in this wonderful concert, recorded at Château de Chantilly, France. The ‘Grande Dame' of the piano is joined by various renowned artists, including pianists Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shaï, and Arielle Beck violinists Gidon Kremer, Maxim Vengerov, and Tedi Papavrami cellist Mischa Maisky, Flugelhorn player Sergei Nakariakov, as well as her daughter and grandson: Lyda Chen-Argerich (piano and viola) and David Chen-Argerich (piano). On the program are Alfred Schnittke's Congratulatory rondo for piano and violin Preludes No. 5, 21, and 24 from Mieczysław Weinberg's 24 Preludes, Op. 100 (arranged for solo violin by G. Kremer) ‘Waltz' and ‘Slava' from Sergei Rachmaninoff's 6 Morceaux, Op. 11, and Romance for six hands Fritz Kreisler's Liebesleid Robert Schumann's Fantasiestücke Op. 73, and Piano Quintet in E-flat major, Op. 44 and ‘Laideronnette, impératrice des Pagodes' from Maurice Ravel's Ma mère l'Oye. This performance was recorded on June 11, 2021.

programme.title: Tuva Semmingsen, Klaus Tönshoff, Danish National Symphony Orchestra & DR Big Band
programme.desc: Musicians of the Danish National Symphony Orchestra, the DR Big Band, and the Danish National Vocal Ensemble join forces under the baton of Klaus Tönshoff in this dazzling concert featuring great songs from black and white cinema. Norwegian mezzosoprano Tuva Semmingsen sings ‘Diamonds Are A Girl's Best Friend', from Gentlemen Prefer Blondes, ‘My Favorite Things' from The Sound of Music, ‘Over the Rainbow' from The Wizard of Oz, ‘Moon River' from Breakfast at Tiffany's, and many other unforgettable hits. This concert performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in June 2020.

programme.title: Maria Luigia Borsi & Antonio Artese
programme.sub-title: Vocal works by Puccini, Leoncavallo a. o.
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Maria Luigia Borsi (soprano) and Antonio Artese (piano) present a recital consisting of several songs and arias. On the program are Francesco Paolo Tosti's Sogno, ‘A vucchella, and L'alba separa dalla luce l'ombra Giacomo Puccini's Sole e amore, Sogno d'or, “Donde lieta” (from La Bohème), “Il bel sogno di Doretta” (from La rondine), and “O mio babbino caro” (from Gianni Schicchi) Renato Brogi's Presentimento, Ruggero Leoncavallo's Mattinata, and Alfredo Catalini's Chanson Groenlandaise.

programme.title: Jos van Immerseel, Anima Eterna Brugge, Claron McFadden & Bart Van Caenegem
programme.desc: Belgian conductor Jos van Immerseel leads Anima Eterna Brugge in a concert program dedicated to American composer George Gershwin. The program opens with Gershwin's symphonic suite Catfish Row (arr. Steven D. Bowen) which is based upon music from his famous opera Porgy and Bess (1935). This is followed by the well-known tone poem An American in Paris (1928). After, soprano Claron McFadden joins the orchestra, presenting a selection of Gershwin's classic jazz songs, including ‘The man I love' (1924-27), ‘I got rhythm' (1930), and ‘By Strauss' (1936). She also performs ‘My man's gone now' and ‘Summertime' from Porgy and Bess. The concert ends with Gershwin's celebrated Rhapsody in Blue, with Bart Van Caenegem as featured pianist. This performance was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, on March 3, 2017.

programme.desc: Los duques de Coburgo parecían condenados a la insignificancia. Gracias a una hábil política matrimonial, en el siglo XIX logran un ascenso meteórico hasta convertirse en la dinastía más importante de su tiempo. Fundaron las casas reales de Bélgica y Bulgaria, gobernaron Inglaterra y Portugal y se casaron en los palacios de toda Europa.

programme.title: Rey sin corona
programme.desc: "Rey sin Corona" explora la historia del exrey Constantino II, su breve reinado y exilio. Entre entrevistas y material de archivo, el documental revela los desafíos de la familia real griega, desde la abolición de la monarquía hasta su regreso a Grecia. Sin buscar el poder, Constantino solo desea pasar sus últimos días en su tierra natal, mientras reflexiona sobre el futuro de Grecia.

programme.title: Los Grimaldi
programme.desc: Los Grimaldi - La Nobleza Obliga explora la vida glamorosa de la familia principesca de Mónaco, llena de escándalos, destino y lujo. Este documental presenta imágenes raras, incluyendo una película amateur de la boda entre el Príncipe Rainiero y Grace Kelly. Además, miembros de la alta nobleza europea y el director Robert Dornhelm comparten sus experiencias y anécdotas. Entrevistas con biógrafos y amigos de la familia ofrecen una visión fascinante de esta dinastía llena de brillo y glamour.

programme.title: The New Frontier
programme.sub-title: S04:E10 - Where are all the Aliens?
programme.desc: Stiamo cercando a fondo, ma i numeri non tornano. È davvero così difficile trovare la vita su altri pianeti? Esiste? Non abbiamo scoperto nemmeno un segnale, quindi forse siamo davvero soli nel nostro angolo di galassia.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature
programme.desc: In questa puntata viaggiamo dal Sud al Nord della Terra Santa, in Israele, fermandoci ad ammirare i panorami e a cogliere l'importanza biblica dei siti storici. Proseguiamo verso le alture del Golan, nel Nord, dove il recente conflitto è ancora molto evidente, e concludiamo il nostro pellegrinaggio sulle rive della Galilea.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature
programme.desc: Molte isole si trovano nel mare tra la Gran Bretagna e la Scandinavia. Tutte queste isole sarebbero rimaste innevate e la vita non sarebbe stata sostenibile se non fosse stato per la Corrente del Golfo. Le acque calde che scorrono attraverso l'Oceano Atlantico fino al Sud America spiegano il clima mite delle isole, la loro ricchezza naturale e la loro storia millenaria. Queste sono le tre isole che stiamo per visitare nella puntata di oggi di Miracoli della natura: Vesterålen, Fair Isle e Orkneys.

programme.title: Dropped

programme.title: Herbie Hancock & The Headhunter
programme.desc: American keyboard player and bandleader Herbie Hancock (1940) achieved success as an incisive, harmonically provocative jazz pianist in the 1960s, then went on to gain wide popularity as a leader of electric jazz-rock groups. One of these, Hancock's band The Headhunters, ushered in a new era of jazz that appealed to a far wider audience, making jazz listeners out of rhythm and blues fans, and vice versa. In 1974, The Headhunters appeared on German television, playing Palm Grease, Sly, Butterfly, Spank-A-Lee, and Chameleon. Hancock (keys) is joined by Bennie Maupin (saxophones), Paul Jackson (electric bass), Mike Clark (drums) and Bill Summer (percussion).

programme.title: Ella Fitzgerald
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Avishai Cohen
programme.desc: Double bassist Avishai Cohen's trio with Noam David (drums) and Omri Mor (pianist) joined forces with the international Symphony Orchestra ‘INSO-Lviv', conducted by Christian Schumann. On June 24, 2017 they brought Avishai Cohen's signature blend of influences from Eastern Europe, American jazz and the Middle East to the Alfa Jazz Festival in Lviv, Ukraine. Cohen, who also supplies vocalizations in the Judeo-Spanish dialect Ladino, came to prominence internationally in the 1990s when jazz great Chick Corea offered him a place in his trio and a recording deal. Thirty years later, Cohen has become a house-hold name himself, leaving his Ukrainian audience enthralled and connected through the universal language of music.

programme.title: Trombone Shorty
programme.sub-title: Troy 'Trombone Shorty' Andrews: Jazz à Vienne
programme.desc: Jazz phenomenon Trombone Shorty dishes out a mix of funk, jazz, hip-hop and soul at this concert at the French festival Jazz à Vienne. Playing with the energy of a rock star, Troy Andrews, a.k.a. ‘Trombone Shorty', pays homage to jazz legends. With his hypnotic performance and boundless energy, Trombone Shorty puts up an unparalleled performance.

programme.title: Miles Davis
programme.desc: American trumpeter Miles Davis (1926-1991) was a pioneering jazz musician from the late 1940s to the late 1980s. His influence on 20th century music is hard to overstate, as he trailblazed bebop, cool jazz, hardbop, modal jazz, and electronic music. On October 11, 1964, Miles Davis performed at Teatro Dell'Arte in Milan. With tenor saxophonist Wayne Shorter, pianist Herbie Hancock, bassist Ron Carter and drummer Tony Williams, Davis performed Autumn Leaves, My Funny Valentine, All Blues, All of You, and Joshua.

programme.title: George Shearing & Neil Swanson
programme.sub-title: George Shearing Duo feat. Neil Swainson
programme.desc: British pianist George Shearing enjoyed an international reputation as an instrumentalist, arranger, and composer. Equally at home on the classical concert stage as in jazz clubs, he was recognized for his inventive, orchestrated jazz. In this live recording from the Munich Philharmonie, Shearing played in a duo format with Canadian double bassist Neil Swainson. The repertoire consisted of a selection of compositions by Shearing himself, among them ‘Lullaby Of Birdland', which is a standard in jazz repertoire.

programme.title: Cannonball Adderley, Nat Adderley, Yusuf Lateef & Joe Zawinul
programme.desc: Cannonball Adderley: Live in '63 boasts two beautifully filmed concerts from one of the most celebrated sextets in jazz history, captured at the top of their game. Cannonball Adderley (alto sax), Nat Adderley (cornet), and the masterful Yusef Lateef (tenor sax, flute, oboe), provide a massive three-horn frontline attack, while the stellar rhythm section featuring a pre-Weather Report Joe Zawinul (piano), Sam Jones (bass), and Louis Hayes (drums) fuel the songs with a deep infectious swing. Quincy Jones' "Jessica's Day" leaps from the gate with a huge big band sound that is extraordinary for only six musicians. This recording is a reminder that Cannonball Adderley was one of the most outstanding and highly respected alto saxophonists in the history of jazz. He was a bluesy jazzman who could play anything in superb fashion.

programme.title: David Bowie
programme.desc: David Bowie was the leading figure in popular music for over five decades. Acclaimed by critics and musicians for his innovative work. His career was marked by reinvention and visual presentation, his music and stagecraft significantly influencing popular music. During his lifetime, his record sales, estimated at 140 million albums worldwide, made him one of the bestselling music artists. He stopped concert touring after 2004 and his last live performance was at a charity event in 2006. In 2013, Bowie returned from a decade-long recording hiatus with the release of The Next Day. He remained musically active until his Death two days after the release of his final album, Blackstar.

programme.title: Michael Jackson
programme.desc: Michael Jackson American singer, songwriter, dancer and simply the King of Pop. His contributions to music, dance, and publicized personal life made him a global figure in popular culture for over four decades. Jackson made his professional debut in 1964 as a member of The Jackson 5, soon becoming a dominant figure in popular music. His music videos, “Beat It", “Billie Jean", and “Thriller" are credited with breaking racism in the USA and transforming the medium into an art form. Thriller is the best-selling album of all time. Jackson was the most awarded recording artist in the history of popular music. Aspects of Jackson's personal life generated controversy and while preparing for his comeback concert series, This Is It, Jackson died of acute Propofol and Benzodiazepine intoxication on June 25, 2009, after suffering from cardiac arrest. The Los Angeles County Department of Medical Examiner Coroner ruled his death a homicide, and his personal physician, Conrad Murray.

programme.title: Leonardo García Alarcón, Cappella Mediterranea & Mariana Flores
programme.sub-title: Vocal baroque works by Cavalli, Strozzi & Bembo
programme.desc: Argentinian conductor and harpsichordist Leonardo García Alarcón leads his ensemble Cappella Mediterranea in a program of Italian Baroque music. The ensemble performs some of the finest Baroque pieces composed by Francesco Cavalli, a prominent composer in 17th-century Venice, and two of his famous students, Barbara Strozzi and Antonia Bembo. Argentinian soprano Mariana Flores presents the vocal works. On the program are ‘Mira questi due lumi' from Cavalli's Le nozze di Teti e di Peleo, ‘Dimmi, Amor, che farò' from L'Oristeo, ‘Sinfonia della notte' from L'Egisto, and ‘E vuol dunque Ciprigna' from Ercole Amante ‘M'ingannasti in verità' from Bembo's Produzioni armoniche consacrate a Luigi XIV Strozzi's Sino alla morte, Che si può fare, Lagrime mie, L'amante segreto, and è Pazzo il moi core Biagio Marini's La Romanesca Tarquinio Merula's Aria Sopra La Cieccona and Dario Castello's Sonata Seconda. This performance was recorded at the magnificent Église Notre-Dame of Sablé-sur-Sarthe, France, on August 26, 2020.

programme.title: Les Arts Florissants & Paul Agnew
programme.desc: Italian composer Claudio Monteverdi (1567-1643) composed nine books of madrigals in half a century, which helped transform the genre from the polyphonic, a cappella madrigals of the late Renaissance to the ‘concertato' madrigals of the early Baroque, shifting the style's focus to the ability of music to express emotions contained in a text. In 2011, British tenor Paul Agnew and renowned Baroque ensemble Les Arts Florissants started recording eight books of Monteverdi's madrigals. In this program, Agnew leads Les Arts Florissants in the madrigals of Book I. Published on New Year's day of 1587, Book I consist of seventeen madrigals for five voices. This performance was recorded at the Cité de la musique in Paris, France, in 2011.

programme.title: Martha Argerich, Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shai & Arielle Beck
programme.sub-title: Martha Argerich – A Birthday Celebration - I
programme.desc: On the occasion of her 80th birthday, Argentinian pianist Martha Argerich explored chamber music repertoire in this wonderful concert, recorded at Château de Chantilly, France. The ‘Grande Dame' of the piano is joined by various renowned artists, including pianists Evgeny Kissin, Iddo Bar-Shaï, and Arielle Beck violinists Gidon Kremer, Maxim Vengerov, and Tedi Papavrami cellist Mischa Maisky, Flugelhorn player Sergei Nakariakov, as well as her daughter and grandson: Lyda Chen-Argerich (piano and viola) and David Chen-Argerich (piano). On the program are Alfred Schnittke's Congratulatory rondo for piano and violin Preludes No. 5, 21, and 24 from Mieczysław Weinberg's 24 Preludes, Op. 100 (arranged for solo violin by G. Kremer) ‘Waltz' and ‘Slava' from Sergei Rachmaninoff's 6 Morceaux, Op. 11, and Romance for six hands Fritz Kreisler's Liebesleid Robert Schumann's Fantasiestücke Op. 73, and Piano Quintet in E-flat major, Op. 44 and ‘Laideronnette, impératrice des Pagodes' from Maurice Ravel's Ma mère l'Oye. This performance was recorded on June 11, 2021.

programme.title: Tuva Semmingsen, Klaus Tönshoff, Danish National Symphony Orchestra & DR Big Band
programme.desc: Musicians of the Danish National Symphony Orchestra, the DR Big Band, and the Danish National Vocal Ensemble join forces under the baton of Klaus Tönshoff in this dazzling concert featuring great songs from black and white cinema. Norwegian mezzosoprano Tuva Semmingsen sings ‘Diamonds Are A Girl's Best Friend', from Gentlemen Prefer Blondes, ‘My Favorite Things' from The Sound of Music, ‘Over the Rainbow' from The Wizard of Oz, ‘Moon River' from Breakfast at Tiffany's, and many other unforgettable hits. This concert performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in June 2020.

programme.title: Maria Luigia Borsi & Antonio Artese
programme.sub-title: Vocal works by Puccini, Leoncavallo a. o.
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Maria Luigia Borsi (soprano) and Antonio Artese (piano) present a recital consisting of several songs and arias. On the program are Francesco Paolo Tosti's Sogno, ‘A vucchella, and L'alba separa dalla luce l'ombra Giacomo Puccini's Sole e amore, Sogno d'or, “Donde lieta” (from La Bohème), “Il bel sogno di Doretta” (from La rondine), and “O mio babbino caro” (from Gianni Schicchi) Renato Brogi's Presentimento, Ruggero Leoncavallo's Mattinata, and Alfredo Catalini's Chanson Groenlandaise.

programme.title: Jos van Immerseel, Anima Eterna Brugge, Claron McFadden & Bart Van Caenegem
programme.desc: Belgian conductor Jos van Immerseel leads Anima Eterna Brugge in a concert program dedicated to American composer George Gershwin. The program opens with Gershwin's symphonic suite Catfish Row (arr. Steven D. Bowen) which is based upon music from his famous opera Porgy and Bess (1935). This is followed by the well-known tone poem An American in Paris (1928). After, soprano Claron McFadden joins the orchestra, presenting a selection of Gershwin's classic jazz songs, including ‘The man I love' (1924-27), ‘I got rhythm' (1930), and ‘By Strauss' (1936). She also performs ‘My man's gone now' and ‘Summertime' from Porgy and Bess. The concert ends with Gershwin's celebrated Rhapsody in Blue, with Bart Van Caenegem as featured pianist. This performance was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, on March 3, 2017.
